---
layout: layouts/page.njk
title: "VoiceTel Phone"
description: "VoiceTel Phone provides web, desktop, and mobile VoIP calling backed by VoiceTel SIP credentials with WebRTC media, call history, DTMF, and diagnostics."
---

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "Service",
	"serviceType": "VoIP calling application",
	"name": "VoiceTel Phone",
	"provider": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.brand }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" },
	"areaServed": ["US", "CA"],
	"url": "{{ site.url }}/phone/",
	"description": "VoIP calling application for web, Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, and Android. SIP-over-TLS, WebRTC media, DTMF, caller-ID, call history, real-time SIP logging, and NAT-friendly registration."
}
</script>

<p class="eyebrow">Phone applications</p>
<h1>One calling experience across web, desktop, and mobile.</h1>
<p class="lede">One app, three form factors — same crystal-clear calling. VoiceTel Phone gives users a clean calling surface for web, Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, and Android while keeping provisioning tied to VoiceTel SIP credentials and account controls.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/phone/applications/web/">Open web phone</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/phone/applications/">All applications</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>App features</h2>
	<ul class="features-grid">
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "telephone" %}</span>
			<h3>Web calling</h3>
			<p>Start calls from the browser without a desktop install where WebRTC is supported.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "layers" %}</span>
			<h3>Desktop apps</h3>
			<p>Support Windows, macOS, and Linux users with the same VoiceTel identity.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "phone-vibrate" %}</span>
			<h3>Mobile apps</h3>
			<p>Keep users reachable on iOS and Android where mobile deployment is enabled.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "shield-check" %}</span>
			<h3>WebRTC media</h3>
			<p>Modern browser media via WebRTC, with DTLS-SRTP for the media path where supported by the runtime.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "record-circle" %}</span>
			<h3>Call recording</h3>
			<p>Record calls for compliance, training, or QA.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "activity" %}</span>
			<h3>Diagnostics</h3>
			<p>Expose call history, DTMF behavior, and SIP message logging for troubleshooting.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "tag" %}</span>
			<h3>Private Label</h3>
			<p>Custom branding and licensing opportunities for resellers and integrators.</p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="phone-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="phone-cta-heading">Get the apps.</h2>
	<p>Sign up to provision and obtain SIP credentials, then grab the apps for every platform. For private-label, white-label, or partner-licensing inquiries, contact us.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/signup/">Sign up</a>
		<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact/">Contact us</a>
	</p>
</aside>
